In the early 20th century, Albert Einstein revolutionized our understanding of space and time with his theory of special relativity. This theory introduced the concept of spacetime, a four-dimensional continuum where the three dimensions of space and one dimension of time are intertwined. Einstein's work laid the foundation for modern physics and has been experimentally verified countless times, shaping our view of the universe.
